    FAQs

    What are the engine specifications of Yamaha YZF R15 V3 ?
    The Yamaha R15 V3 comes with a 155.1 cc liquid-cooled, single-cylinder, fuel-injected, SOHC engine. The engine generates a power of 19.30 HP at 10,000 rpm and a maximum torque of 15 Nm at 8500 rpm. This engine is complemented with a six-speed gearbox. The bike comes with Variable Valve Actuation technology that regulates fuel at different speeds and throttle inputs.
    Yes
    No
    Is Yamaha YZF R15 V3 similar in design to the R-series ?
    Yes, Yamaha YZF R15 V3 has been inspired by the R-series bikes, like those belonging to R3 and R6 series. However, it has angular headlamps that have been separated by a central vent. This fully-faired bike comes with numerous next-gen features.
    Yes
    No
    What mileage does the bike give ?
    Equipped with the displacement engine of 155.1cc, the YZF R15 V3 offers an ARAI certified mileage of approximately 35 to 45 kmpl.
    Yes
    No
    Is it worthwhile to buy the Yamaha YZF R15 V3 ?
    With a superior design, and outstanding comfort and performance, the YZF R15 V3 is one of the sportiest bikes you will find in this segment. Its price is affordable and offers good mileage and performance for a fully-faired bike.

    Yamaha R15 v3 (Racing Blue) Overview

     

    The Yamaha R15 altered the landscape of sports bikes in the country, and the Yamaha R15 V3 model shifted from functional to becoming performance-centric. This Yamaha bike was unveiled in the Indian market on January 8, 2018, and features a high-performance VVA system. It also comes with an assist and slipper clutch, which reduces fatigue and facilitates smooth and enjoyable downshifts. This sports bike has a braking system that includes front and rear disc brakes, with a dual-channel ABS as a safety net.

     

    The Yamaha R15 V3 also sports a lower pillion seat, which enhances convenience. The bike’s underpinnings include telescopic front forks and a rear mono-shock, which handle its suspension tasks.

    Yamaha YZF R15 v3 Racing Blue price and specifications

     

    On Bajaj Mall, the Yamaha R15 V3 price for the Racing Blue variant is Rs. 1,63,400 (ex-showroom, Delhi). The two-wheeler employs 17-inch alloy wheels on both ends and has a kerb weight of 142 Kg. Here are a few of the key specifications of the model :

     

    Performance :

    If you are riding on highways, the Yamaha R15 V3 can clock up to 136 kmph. The bike can accelerate from 0-60 Kmph in just under 4 seconds and from 0-100 in 11.42 seconds! Moreover, its fuel tank capacity of 11 litres reduces the number of times you need to make emergency stops at filling stations. The fuel efficiency range of this two-wheeler is around 517 Km, making it a fuel-efficient and high-performance bike.

     

    Design :

    Borrowing its design elements and styling cues from Yamaha R6, the Yamaha R15 V3 is a certified head-turner. It flaunts all-LED lamps and an all-digital LCD instrument cluster that provides comprehensive information about the bike’s performance. The bike also has a sculpted body that lends it a sporty look.

     

    Engine and transmission :

    The Yamaha R15 V3 runs on a 155 cc single-cylinder, four-valve, four-stroke, FI, liquid-cooled, BS 6-compliant engine that churns out a peak power of 18.6 PS. It also generates a peak torque of 14.1 Nm, and the engine is mated to a 6-speed manual transmission. This provides quick acceleration and more power while facilitating relaxed cruising on the highways.

     

    Colour options :

    This sports bike from Yamaha comes in four colour options – Racing Blue, Metallic Red, Metallic Grey, and Dark Knight.

     

    Mileage :

    As per ARAI, this two-wheeler offers a fuel economy of 48.75 kmpl. However, the owner-reported mileage ranges from 45-48.75 kmpl. On highways, this bike offers a mileage close to 50 Kmpl.

     

    Key specifications of the Yamaha R15 V3

     

    The Yamaha R15 V3 is a high-performance bike equipped with a powerful 155cc engine that delivers a power of 18.6 PS and a peak torque of 14.1 Nm. It comes with disc brakes at both ends for enhanced stopping power. It is renowned for its superior fuel efficiency with a mileage of 48.75 kmpl. The R15 V3 features tubeless tyres that provide added safety and convenience in case of punctures. Design-wise, the bike embraces a sporty look, following the design paradigm of the Yamaha R series. The bike also boasts safety features that make it a reliable option for both city commutes and long rides.
